idinfo.datacred:
These instructions describe watershed delineation using 10 meter digital elevation models (DEM) in ARCGRID. With a snap distance of 40 meters in the snappour function, use a pour point approximately five rows above the insertion as indicated by stream coverage rivercov10.
Example: 1. Log on into Exceed 2. Open an AIX window in Exceed. 3. Navigate to a directory that has the following files (directories) available using the cd command (e.g. cd /fsfiles/unit/research/kingsriver/big/1order): a. accumkrgrd b. flowkrgrd c. rivercov10 ARCINFO coverage d. any other coverage necessary to make finding insertion point easier. 4. Start ARC (type arc)
